@Willdotwhite I think we are looking for confidence that moving to the Java code for system information works well in both windows and linux.  I often look at the .bats test and repeat those steps in my manual testing...    I suppose also testing the pass in --solr-url would be interesting.   You could test against this demo Solr: 

http://quepid-solr.dev.o19s.com:8985/solr/media/select?q=Example is Solr 8.11 w/ images and Basic Auth setting solr:SolrRocks and http links

So...  `bin/solr.cmd status --solr-url http://quepid-solr.dev.o19s.com:8985 -u solr:SolrRocks' would be interesting, especially cause it's 8.11 not 10!
